@karock Thanks!

Looks like the latency of reading `/proc/<pid>smaps` is correlated to process memory size, so reading it every second is definitely not a good idea. 

@oranagra @YaacovHazan I think we'll need to drop the frequency of reporting CoW significantly, or make it otherwise adaptive.   It seems like there's no other, more efficient way to get this information.
